Paris Saint Germain forward Maxim Choupo-Moting’s proposed transfer to Leece is now in doubt, according to L’Equipe. The deal is being held up because Choupo-Moting is reluctant to take a pay cut. Lecce’s offer is for one year, with the option for a further two years, should they beat the drop this season. The 30-year-old, who moved to PSG from Stoke City last summer, has one year left on his current contract at Parc des Princes. Choupo-Moting featured in 22 Ligue 1 matches for PSG last term, scoring three goals. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.